'''''A New Expression of the Earth: the experiences of the European Ceramics Work Centre''''' was the name of an international exhibition of [[contemporary art]] held at the [[Luis Seoane Foundation]], [[A Coruña]], [[Spain]], 11 December 1997 – 31 January 1998.<ref>Xavier Toubes, ''[http://archive.balticmill.com/?itemid=3144 A New Expression of the Earth: the experiences of the European Ceramics Work Centre]'', Stedelijk Van Abbemuseum, Eindhoven, the Netherlands.</ref>
== Featured artists == The exhibition showed the experiences of seventeen artists at the [[European Ceramics Work Centre]] after working there during the year 1997. It included works by:
{| | width="33%" valign="top"| * [[Caro Bensca]] * [[Marek Cecula]] * [[Madeleine Child]] * [[Tony Cragg]] * [[Tony Hepburn]] * [[Netty V. D. Heuvel]] | width="33%" valign="top"| * [[Leiko Ikemura]] * [[Jun Kaneko]] * [[Bhupen Khakhar]] * [[Daniel Kruger]] * [[Geert Lap]] * [[Mark Manders]] | width="33%" valign="top"| * [[Víctor Mira]] * [[Anne - Marie Van Sprang]] * [[Helly Oestreicher]] * [[Norbert Prangenberg]] * [[Anita Wong]] |}
==Notes== * A catalogue was published on behalf of this exhibition by the Luis Seoane Foundation (Fundación Luis Seone) & The European Ceramics Work Centre in 1992 entitled: "A new expression of the earth: the experiences of the European Ceramics Work Centre" = "A nova expresión da terra: as experiencias do European Ceramics Work Centre" = "La nueva expresión de la tierra: las experiencias del European Ceramics Work Centre"; authors: Xavier Toubes and the artists.
