'''''Hay Harvest at Éragny''''' (French: Fenaison à Éragny) is a 1901 painting by [[France|French]] [[Impressionism|Impressionist]] [[Painting|painter]] [[Camille Pissarro]] depicting the hay harvest in the [[Commune in France|French commune]] of [[Éragny-sur-Epte]].

It is currently in the collection of the [[National Gallery of Canada]].

