'''Iran’s House of Art''' is a [[University of Minnesota]]-affiliated non-profit organization dedicated to improving the public's understanding of [[Iran]] by arranging for art exhibitions, film screenings, lectures and concerts by Iranian musicians. Originally conceived by [[Aida Shahghasemi]], the organization was established in the 2007-2008 academic year, and has held a number of successful events at the university, beginning with "Merge: Harmony of Mystic Words".<ref>{{Citation | last = Mannix | first = Andy | author-link = | last2 = | first2 = | author2-link = | title = New student group presents Iranian art | newspaper = Minnesota Daily | pages = 1 | date = November 12, 2007 | url = http://www.mndaily.com/2007/11/12/new-student-group-presents-iranian-art }}</ref>
