{{BLP sources|date=April 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2012}} {{Use British English|date=July 2012}} {{Infobox person | name = Sarah Pia Anderson | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | othername = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[St Albans]], UK | death_date = | death_place = | alma_mater = | occupation = Television director, theatre director | years_active = 1979–present | spouse = | website = }}
'''Sarah Pia Anderson''' (born 1952) is an English born television and theatre director.<ref name="Film Reference">[http://www.filmreference.com/film/26/Sarah-Pia-Anderson.html Sarah Pia Anderson Biography (1952-)], Film Reference</ref>
Her career in the theatre included work for the [[Royal National Theatre|National Theatre]]: ''[[Rosmersholm]]'', the [[Royal Shakespeare Company]]: ''Mary and Lizzie'' and the [[Abbey Theatre]]: ''[[Carthaginians]]''.<ref name="Film Reference" /> Her early television work included ''Prime Suspect 4: Inner Circles'' (1995), starring [[Helen Mirren]]. She has worked mainly in the United States since the mid-1990s, directing episodes of ''[[Dark Angel (2000 TV series)|Dark Angel]]'', ''[[Gilmore Girls]]'', ''[[Dead Like Me]]'', ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', ''[[Veronica Mars]]'' and other series. In 2011, she directed the opening episodes of ''[[Scott & Bailey]]'' produced by RED Production Company for ITV1.
She is currently a professor in the Cinema and Technocultural Studies Program at [[University of California, Davis]].<ref>[http://www.news.ucdavis.edu/search/news_detail.lasso?id=9393 UC Davis News & Information :: Sarah Pia Anderson] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120805180210/http://www.news.ucdavis.edu/search/news_detail.lasso?id=9393 |date=5 August 2012 }}</ref>
